%% Mermaid sequence diagram for restore lifecycle
sequenceDiagram
  participant CLI as CLI
  participant API as API Service
  participant DB as MySQL Queue
  participant W as Worker Service
  participant S3 as AWS S3
  participant MySQL as MySQL Host

  CLI->>API: POST /api/jobs (user, customer, dbhost, overwrite)
  API->>API: Validate options, generate user_code, target
  API->>DB: Check for existing queued/running jobs
  API->>DB: INSERT job (status=queued)
  API-->>CLI: 201 Created {job_id, target, status}
  W->>DB: Poll for queued jobs
  W->>DB: Acquire lock + mark running
  W->>S3: Fetch latest backup
  W->>W: Verify disk space
  W->>W: Extract archive to workspace
  W->>MySQL: Cleanup orphaned staging databases
  W->>MySQL: Run myloader restore to staging_name
  W->>MySQL: Execute post-restore SQL scripts on staging
  W->>MySQL: Add pullDB metadata table to staging
  W->>MySQL: Atomic rename staging tables to target
  W->>MySQL: Drop staging database
  W->>DB: Mark complete + append events
  CLI->>API: GET /api/jobs (status query)
  API->>DB: Query job status
  API-->>CLI: 200 OK {job status, events}

